<recipeml version="0.5">
  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple Jello Salad</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Salads &amp; dr</cat>
        <cat>To post</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Red Cinnamon Candy Drops</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Boiling Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>packages</unit></amt>
        <item>(Small) Red Jello; &lt;OR&gt;</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3</qty>
          <unit>packages</unit></amt>
        <item>(Small) Combination Flavor Jello</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2 1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Cold Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4 1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Grated Apples; unpeeled</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>cup</unit></amt>
        <item>Pecans; chopped</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Dissolve 3/4 cup red cinnamon candy drops in the boiling water. Add jello.
  When all is dissolved and 2 1/4 cups cold water. Stir in 4 1/2 cups grated
  apples and chopped pecans. Pour in mold or 9 x 13 pan. Chill till set.
  
  Serve on lettuce leaf if desired.
  
  Source: Recipes Out of This World Women of St. Agnes Catholic Church
  Charleston, WV 1969
  
